      "usage": "Takamagahara is the source of cosmic order and divine authority in Shinto cosmology. All kami trace their origins to this celestial realm. The Japanese Imperial family claims descent from Amaterasu, making Takamagahara the ultimate source of Imperial legitimacy. The realm is not just a physical place but represents the principle of divine order that governs reality. Communication between Takamagahara and the earthly realm occurs through ritual, with kami descending to shrines when called and returning to heaven after bestowing blessings.",
      "names": [
        "Takamagahara (È´òÂ§©Âéü) - Plain of High Heaven",
